==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Macaranga gum
<hw>Mac`a*ran"ga gum`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A gum of a crimson color,
obtained from a tree (<spn>Macaranga Indica</spn>) that grows in the
East Indies. It is used in taking impressions of coins, medallions,
etc., and sometimes as a medicine.</def> <rj><au>Balfour (Cyc. of
India).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>macarena</ent>⟦br⟧
